  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Reconstruction, renovation and re-roofing of temporary shelters for IDPs in central Rakhine</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">By the end of the project activity which support to Temporary Shelter for conflicted affected IDP people in Maw Ti Ngar and Thet Kae Pyin displacement sites in Sittwe, the families, who do not have their own unit due to the fully damaged nature of the shelter will be fully reconstructed. Some major damaged shelters will be renovated and some will be reroofing. The 1768 IDP families have improved their living life with ensuring safety, dignity and more resilience to manage for their life saving condition. Especially Women, girls and children are benefitted to receive newly reconstructed, renovated and reroofing shelters for their better living condition to the upcoming monsoon season.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Given the limitations of this allocation, it has been calculated that 30 shelters are targeted for re-roofing, and subsequent re-lining of the kitchen for those same shelters. These shelters will be selected after a rapid technical expertise identifying and prioritizing which roofs have been the most badly damaged and leave the households most exposed in Maw Ti Ngar and Thet Kae Pyin displacement sites of Central Rakhine. The total number is estimated at 1,321 individuals.
Furthermore, the total beneficiary group for the reconstruction and renovation of 11 shelters has been targeted through two needs assessments carried out by NRC and CA which shelters were in urgent need of reconstruction or renovation, based on the condition of roof, ceiling and walls. Total target for this intervention will be 88 households with 447 individuals (207 M, 240 F).</narrative>
  </description>
